  "notes": "## Zone 3 Health Monitoring & Backup Alerts\n\n### Setup Required\n1. **Tailscale**: Ensure n8n Docker container can resolve 'uptime-kuma-pi4' via Tailscale MagicDNS. Add Tailscale sidecar or host networking if needed.\n2. **Telegram**: Create bot via @BotFather, get TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN. Get chat ID via @userinfobot. Set TELEGRAM_CTO_CHAT_ID and TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN env vars.\n3. **Email**: Set ALERT_EMAIL_WEBHOOK_URL (or use SMTP n8n node) and CTO_EMAIL env vars.\n4. **Supabase notifications table**: Must have columns: type, severity, title, message, details, alerted_at, alert_sent.\n\n### Services Monitored\n- Uptime Kuma on Raspberry Pi 4 (Zone 3) via Tailscale: http://uptime-kuma-pi4:3001\n- Backend Zone 2 Python API: http://backend:8001/health\n- All monitors registered in Uptime Kuma status page 'main'\n\n### Alert Channels\n1. Telegram message to CTO chat\n2. Email via backend notification service\n3. Supabase notifications table log\n\n### Reduce Noise\n- Consider adding a 'cooldown' check: only alert if service was healthy in last check (avoid repeated alerts for sustained outages)\n- Use n8n static data or Supabase to track last alert time per service"
}
